// @test regression/variable-shadowing
// @description TV's CW10013/CW10011 shadow warnings (probed 2026-06-04, INV020). CW10013 fires on any declaration form (plain =, var, typed, tuple member, loop iterator) in a non-global scope whose name was declared EARLIER (source order) in an enclosing scope. CW10011 fires for built-in VARIABLE names in any scope and any form; built-in function/namespace names are silent. Negatives pinned here: function params do not warn (h's param a), and a parent declared AFTER the local scope does not warn (g's local e vs global e on the next line).
// @expects parse: success
// @expects warnings: 5
// @expects warning: line=14, message="The function 'ta.sma' should be called"
// @expects warning: line=14, message="Shadowing variable 'a' which exists in parent scope"
// @expects warning: line=15, message="Shadowing variable 'b' which exists in parent scope"
// @expects warning: line=16, message="Shadowing built-in variable 'hl2'"
// @expects warning: line=18, message="Shadowing variable 'i' which exists in parent scope"
//@version=6
indicator("x")
a = 0.0
b = 0.0
i = 0
h(a) =>
    loc = a * 2
    loc
g() =>
    e = 1.0
    e
e = 2.0
if close > open
    a = ta.sma(close, 14)
    var b = 2.0
    hl2 = 1.0
    label.new(bar_index, a + b + hl2)
for i = 0 to 3
    label.new(i, close)
plot(a + b + e + i + h(close) + g())
